quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,26,"Those who are kafir say, ´Do not listen to this Qur´an. Drown it out so that hopefully you will gain the upper hand.´"
  41,27,We will make those who are kafir suffer a severe punishment and repay them for the worst of what they did
  41,28,That is the repayment of the enemies of Allah — the Fire. They will have it for their Eternal Home as repayment for their renunciation of Our Signs
  41,29,"Those who are kafir say, ´Our Lord, show us those jinn and men who misguided us and we will place them beneath our feet so that they will be among the lowest of the low.´"
  41,30,"The angels descend on those who say, ´Our Lord is Allah,´ and then go straight: ´Do not fear and do not grieve but rejoice in the Garden you have been promised"
  41,31,We are your protectors in the life of this world and the Next World. You will have there all that your selves could wish for. You will have there everything you demand
  41,32,"Hospitality from One who is Ever-Forgiving, Most Merciful.´"